title: Grateful Dead Live at The Spectrum on 1987-03-31
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi CR-7A) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.8 MHz) >KORG AudioGate 4 > Adobe Audition CC 2015 > Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC/24
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw-> Franklin's Tower-> CC Rider, Ramble On Rose, Tons Of Steel, Mama Tried-> Big River, Candyman, Desolation Row, Don't Ease Me In

Set 2

Touch Of Gray, Estimated Prophet, Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Space-> Uncle John's Band-> I Need A Miracle-> Stella Blue-> Around & Around-> Turn On Your Love Light, E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text: Didn't take much My first show, my older brother took me. It didn't take very much, I wandered the lot and was hooked. Felt right at home. Then got inside and then boys pulled this one out. Thanks Charlie for the beautiful stuff as always. It takes me back to my mid-teen years of when i got on the bus and started the time of my life.
